      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i've been noticing something weird lately... i think the crows in my neighborhood are actually signaling weather changes before they happen. like, yesterday they all started a specific rhythmic tapping on the power lines right before the storm hit, and it was almost like they were coordinated. has anyone else ever noticed this kind of patterns in birds? it feels like they're communicating something specific about the pressure dropping.",
