    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just instinct though. it's like they're using a specific code. i've been tracking the sequences and it's not random at all. when the tapping follows a 3-beat pattern, it's always a heavy rain within an hour. but when they do this low, continuous warbling in the trees, it's a clear sign of a heatwave coming. i feel like i'm finally starting to decrypt what they're actually saying. do you think it's possible they've developed a way to communicate meteorological data to each other?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
